<subSubSection id="B882655EFF83FFDB1BA3F46B9397FA3B" pageId="70" pageNumber="199" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="F02736D5FF83FFDB1BA3F46B9397FA3B" blockId="70.[166,794,1906,2017]" lastBlockId="70.[839,1467,1218,1476]" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF83FFDB1BA3F46B9639F875" bold="true" box="[166,284,1906,1930]" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Head with rostrum anteriorly rounded or truncated; eye reniform or oval. Antenna 1 peduncular article 1 ball-shaped proximally; peduncular article 2 medium length or long; callynophore absent in female, present in male. Antenna 2 flagellum about as long as that of antenna 
<quantity id="37609B30FF83FFDB18C6F7F994CAFB08" box="[963,1007,1248,1271]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.54" pageId="70" pageNumber="199" unit="in" value="1.0">1 in</quantity>
female, longer than body in male [where known]. Mandible palp article 3 with proximal A3-seta in male [where known], without proximal A3-seta in female. Pereopod 4 coxa with anterior and posterior margins subparallel or with anterior margin slightly obtuse, posterior margin straight. Uropod 3 rami with plumose setae in male [where known], without plumose setae in female; outer ramus 1-articulate or 2-articulate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
