<subSubSection id="B882655EFF83FFDA1842F5D99568FD5D" lastPageId="71" lastPageNumber="200" pageId="70" pageNumber="199" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F02736D5FF83FFDB1842F5D993D6F8ED" blockId="70.[839,1467,1728,2016]" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF83FFDB1842F5D9948FF927" bold="true" box="[839,938,1728,1752]" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">Remarks</emphasis>
. Within the vijayiine group 
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF83FFDB1FB9F5D893D7F927" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Stoddart" authorityYear="2002" box="[1212,1266,1729,1752]" class="Malacostraca" family="Amaryllididae" genus="Devo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="70" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF83FFDB1FB9F5D893D7F927" box="[1212,1266,1729,1752]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">Devo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF83FFDB1E25F5D8929EF927" authorityName="Pirlot" authorityYear="1933" box="[1312,1467,1729,1752]" class="Malacostraca" family="Amaryllididae" genus="Bathyamaryllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="70" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF83FFDB1E25F5D8929EF927" box="[1312,1467,1729,1752]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">Bathyamaryllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are probably sister taxa. Both have the unusual proximal ballshaped peduncular article 1 on antenna 1.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F02736D5FF83FFDA1860F400950AFF15" blockId="70.[839,1467,1728,2016]" lastBlockId="71.[121,749,153,674]" lastPageId="71" lastPageNumber="200" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">
The deepwater genera 
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF83FFDB1F5FF40093DAF8CF" authorityName="Pirlot" authorityYear="1933" box="[1114,1279,1817,1840]" class="Malacostraca" family="Amaryllididae" genus="Bathyamaryllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="70" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF83FFDB1F5FF40093DAF8CF" box="[1114,1279,1817,1840]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">Bathyamaryllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF83FFDB1E36F4009249F8CF" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Stoddart" authorityYear="2002" box="[1331,1388,1817,1840]" class="Malacostraca" family="Amaryllididae" genus="Devo" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="70" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF83FFDB1E36F4009249F8CF" box="[1331,1388,1817,1840]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">Devo</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are the most widespread amaryllidid genera with species in the Atlantic and the Indo-West Pacific. The Indo-West Pacific species of 
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF83FFDB18C1F468934BF877" authorityName="Pirlot" authorityYear="1933" box="[964,1134,1905,1928]" class="Malacostraca" family="Amaryllididae" genus="Bathyamaryllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="70" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF83FFDB18C1F468934BF877" box="[964,1134,1905,1928]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">Bathyamaryllis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF83FFDB1F87F4689243F877" box="[1154,1382,1905,1928]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF83FFDB1F87F46893D7F877" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Stoddart" authorityYear="2002" box="[1154,1266,1905,1928]" class="Malacostraca" family="Amaryllididae" genus="Bathyamaryllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="70" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kapala">B. kapala</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF83FFDB1E04F4689243F877" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Stoddart" authorityYear="1994" box="[1281,1382,1905,1928]" class="Malacostraca" family="Amaryllididae" genus="Bathyamaryllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="70" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ouvea">B. ouvea</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF83FFDB1EA6F46894B5F859" authorityName="Pirlot" authorityYear="1933" class="Malacostraca" family="Amaryllididae" genus="Bathyamaryllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="70" pageNumber="199" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perezii">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF83FFDB1EA6F46894B5F859" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">B. perezii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) all have a moderately constricted inner ramus on uropod 2 and a 2-articulate outer ramus on uropod 3; the two North Atlantic species (
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF83FFDB1F72F4D093CAF81F" baseAuthorityName="Stebbing" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1143,1263,1993,2016]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Amaryllis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="70" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="haswelli">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF83FFDB1F72F4D093CAF81F" box="[1143,1263,1993,2016]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">B. haswelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF83FFDB1E21F4D09297F81F" baseAuthorityName="Bonnier" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[1316,1458,1993,2016]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Amaryllis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="70" pageNumber="199" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulchellus">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF83FFDB1E21F4D09297F81F" box="[1316,1458,1993,2016]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="199">B. pulchellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) have only a slightly constricted inner ramus on uropod 2 and a 1-articulate uropod 3. These differences suggest two distinct species groups within the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F02736D5FF82FFDA1B92F3E89568FD5D" blockId="71.[121,749,153,674]" pageId="71" pageNumber="200">
Mature males of 
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF82FFDA1A5EF3E8957EFEF7" box="[347,603,241,264]" class="Malacostraca" family="Amaryllididae" genus="Bathyamaryllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="71" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF82FFDA1A5EF3E89524FEF7" box="[347,513,241,264]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="200">Bathyamaryllis</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
are not well known. Males have never been recorded for 
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF82FFDA195DF21795F5FEDA" baseAuthorityName="Stebbing" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[600,720,270,293]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Amaryllis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="71" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="haswelli">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF82FFDA195DF21795F5FEDA" box="[600,720,270,293]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="200">B. haswelli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF82FFDA1B7CF23597C6FEBC" authorityName="Pirlot" authorityYear="1933" box="[121,227,300,323]" class="Malacostraca" family="Amaryllididae" genus="Bathyamaryllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="71" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perezii">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF82FFDA1B7CF23597C6FEBC" box="[121,227,300,323]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="200">B. perezii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The only male known of our new species 
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF82FFDA19D0F23597E7FE9F" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Stoddart" authorityYear="2002" class="Malacostraca" family="Amaryllididae" genus="Bathyamaryllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="71" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kapala">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF82FFDA19D0F23597E7FE9F" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="200">B. kapala</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is immature. 
<bibRefCitation id="94094B24FF82FFDA1A57F2509566FE9F" author="Stephensen, K" box="[338,579,329,352]" pageId="71" pageNumber="200" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref43362" refString="Stephensen, K., 1923. Crustacea Malacostraca, V: (Amphipoda, I). Danish Ingolf-Expedition 3 (8): 1 - 100." type="journal article" year="1923">Stephensen (1923: 44)</bibRefCitation>
reported a male of 
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF82FFDA1B92F27F9600FE82" baseAuthorityName="Bonnier" baseAuthorityYear="1896" box="[151,293,358,381]" class="Liliopsida" family="Amaryllidaceae" genus="Amaryllis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asparagales" pageId="71" pageNumber="200" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pulchellus">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF82FFDA1B92F27F9600FE82" box="[151,293,358,381]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="200">B. pulchellus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in which antenna 2 was “twice as long as antenna 1”, but had no calceoli, and setae were present on article 2 of the mandibular palp. The 
<quantity id="37609B30FF82FFDA191EF2B8954AFE47" box="[539,623,417,440]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.7" pageId="71" pageNumber="200" unit="mm" value="7.7">7.7 mm</quantity>
male of 
<taxonomicName id="37984D56FF82FFDA19D0F2B8979FFE2A" authorityName="Lowry &amp; Stoddart" authorityYear="1994" class="Malacostraca" family="Amaryllididae" genus="Bathyamaryllis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="71" pageNumber="200" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ouvea">
<emphasis id="C2ECEAC7FF82FFDA19D0F2B8979FFE2A" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="200">B. ouvea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
illustrated in Lowry &amp; Stoddart (1994, fig. 7), is immature. The 
<quantity id="37609B30FF82FFDA1A1CF2C29673FE0D" box="[281,342,475,498]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="71" pageNumber="200" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
male of their fig. 10 had both antennae 2 broken; antenna 1 and the remaining articles of antenna 2 had no calceoli; it did have a well-developed callynophore on antenna 1, brush setae on the peduncle of antenna 2, numerous setae on articles 2 and 3 of the mandibular palp, a brush of setae on merus and carpus of pereopods 3 and 4, and plumose setae on the rami of uropod 3.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B882655EFF82FFDA181FF38193E4FF15" pageId="71" pageNumber="200" type="distribution">
